		<text name="systemtxt" extra="true">
			<text>The Super Game Boy is a peripheral that allows Game Boy cartridges to be played on a Super Nintendo Entertainment System console. Released in June 1994, it retailed for $59.99 in the United States and Â£49.99 in the United Kingdom. In South Korea, it is called the Super Mini Comboy and was distributed by Hyundai Electronics. The Super Game Boy is compatible with the same cartridges as the original Game Boy: original Game Boy cartridges, the Game Boy Camera, and dual-mode Game Boy Color cartridges (in Game Boy-mode).</text>
			<pos>0.03 0.39</pos>
			<size>0.42 0.3</size>			
			<backgroundColor>22222200</backgroundColor>
			<fontPath>./../_inc/fonts/FiraSans-Regular.ttf</fontPath>
